If you set a sprite's Y coordinate to 0, it'll be drawn on lines 1 through 8 or 1 through 16 depending on the sprite height switch. So I thought the garbage line for computing sprite priority was the first line of the actual screen, because a sprite can't start on line 0, right? Or does the PPU take two lines to compute sprite priority, doing the first half on line y-1, the second half on line y, and actually displaying the sprite on line y+1?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Dec 23, 2004 6:15 pm</p><hr />
